          "strStadiumDescription": "The Amway Center is a sports and entertainment venue in Orlando, Florida, located in the Downtown area. It is part of Downtown Orlando Master Plan 3: a plan that also involves improvements to the Citrus Bowl and a new performing arts center. The arena is home to the Orlando Magic of the NBA, the Orlando Solar Bears of the ECHL, and hosted the 2012 NBA All-Star Game.\r\n\r\nAmway Center hosted the 2nd and 3rd round games of the NCAA Division I Men’s Basketball Tournament in 2014. On January 14, 2013, the Arena Football League's Board of Directors voted to award ArenaBowl XXVI to Orlando in the summer of 2013. On September 4, 2013, the Orlando Predators were informed that they had defaulted on their lease for failing to meet attendance requirements, forcing the team out of the arena. On April 19, 2014, the venue hosted the UFC on Fox: Werdum vs. Browne mixed martial arts fight.",
